{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":688,"text":"Fifteen years ago, it was widely assumed"},{"time":3577,"text":"that the vast majority of brain development"},{"time":5627,"text":"takes place in the first few years of life."},{"time":8606,"text":"Back then, 15 years ago, we didn't have the ability"},{"time":11318,"text":"to look inside the living human brain"},{"time":13939,"text":"and track development across the lifespan."},{"time":16977,"text":"In the past decade or so, mainly due to advances"},{"time":20138,"text":"in brain imaging technology"},{"time":21943,"text":"such as magnetic resonance imaging, or MRI,"},{"time":24886,"text":"neuroscientists have started to look inside the living"},{"time":28013,"text":"human brain of all ages, and to track changes"},{"time":30432,"text":"in brain structure and brain function,"},{"time":33303,"text":"so we use structural MRI if you'd like to take a snapshot,"},{"time":36980,"text":"a photograph, at really high resolution of the inside"},{"time":40042,"text":"of the living human brain, and we can ask questions like,"},{"time":43262,"text":"how much gray matter does the brain contain,"},{"time":45702,"text":"and how does that change with age?"},{"time":47505,"text":"And we also use functional MRI, called fMRI,"},{"time":51217,"text":"to take a video, a movie, of brain activity"},{"time":54612,"text":"when participants are taking part in some kind of task"},{"time":57480,"text":"like thinking or feeling or perceiving something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60372,"text":"So many labs around the world are involved in this kind"},{"time":63138,"text":"of research, and we now have a really rich"},{"time":65368,"text":"and detailed picture of how the living human brain develops,"},{"time":68892,"text":"and this picture has radically changed the way"},{"time":71960,"text":"we think about human brain development"},{"time":74593,"text":"by revealing that it's not all over in early childhood,"},{"time":77361,"text":"and instead, the brain continues to develop"},{"time":80072,"text":"right throughout adolescence and into the '20s and '30s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84118,"text":"So adolescence is defined as the period of life that starts"},{"time":88097,"text":"with the biological, hormonal, physical changes of puberty"},{"time":92493,"text":"and ends at the age at which an individual attains"},{"time":95778,"text":"a stable, independent role in society."},{"time":99229,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":101019,"text":"It can go on a long time. (Laughter)"},{"time":103784,"text":"One of the brain regions that changes most dramatically"},{"time":106803,"text":"during adolescence is called prefrontal cortex."},{"time":110067,"text":"So this is a model of the human brain,"},{"time":113044,"text":"and this is prefrontal cortex, right at the front."},{"time":115924,"text":"Prefrontal cortex is an interesting brain area."},{"time":118433,"text":"It's proportionally much bigger in humans than"},{"time":121547,"text":"in any other species, and it's involved in a whole range of"},{"time":125190,"text":"high level cognitive functions, things like decision-making,"},{"time":128462,"text":"planning, planning what you're going to do tomorrow"},{"time":130552,"text":"or next week or next year, inhibiting"},{"time":133292,"text":"inappropriate behavior, so stopping yourself saying"},{"time":135958,"text":"something really rude or doing something really stupid."},{"time":138883,"text":"It's also involved in social interaction,"},{"time":140661,"text":"understanding other people, and self-awareness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143785,"text":"So MRI studies looking at the development of this region"},{"time":146835,"text":"have shown that it really undergoes dramatic development"},{"time":149305,"text":"during the period of adolescence."},{"time":152238,"text":"So if you look at gray matter volume, for example,"},{"time":155196,"text":"gray matter volume across age from age four to 22 years"},{"time":160045,"text":"increases during childhood, which is what you can see"},{"time":162367,"text":"on this graph. It peaks in early adolescence."},{"time":166120,"text":"The arrows indicate peak gray matter volume"},{"time":168685,"text":"in prefrontal cortex. You can see that that peak happens"},{"time":172151,"text":"a couple of years later in boys relative to girls,"},{"time":175661,"text":"and that's probably because boys go through puberty"},{"time":177500,"text":"a couple of years later than girls on average,"},{"time":179752,"text":"and then during adolescence, there's a significant decline"},{"time":183187,"text":"in gray matter volume in prefrontal cortex."},{"time":185872,"text":"Now that might sound bad, but actually this is"},{"time":187897,"text":"a really important developmental process, because"},{"time":191047,"text":"gray matter contains cell bodies and connections"},{"time":195153,"text":"between cells, the synapses, and this decline"},{"time":198607,"text":"in gray matter volume during prefrontal cortex"},{"time":201352,"text":"is thought to correspond to synaptic pruning,"},{"time":204244,"text":"the elimination of unwanted synapses."},{"time":206567,"text":"This is a really important process. It's partly dependent"},{"time":209700,"text":"on the environment that the animal or the human is in,"},{"time":212834,"text":"and the synapses that are being used are strengthened,"},{"time":216278,"text":"and synapses that aren't being used"},{"time":218211,"text":"in that particular environment are pruned away."},{"time":220543,"text":"You can think of it a bit like pruning a rosebush."},{"time":223049,"text":"You prune away the weaker branches so that"},{"time":225889,"text":"the remaining, important branches, can grow stronger,"},{"time":228927,"text":"and this process, which effectively fine-tunes brain tissue"},{"time":232853,"text":"according to the species-specific environment,"},{"time":235520,"text":"is happening in prefrontal cortex and in other brain regions"},{"time":238435,"text":"during the period of human adolescence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241989,"text":"So a second line of inquiry that we use to track changes"},{"time":245690,"text":"in the adolescent brain is using functional MRI"},{"time":248942,"text":"to look at changes in brain activity across age."},{"time":252215,"text":"So I'll just give you an example from my lab."},{"time":253857,"text":"So in my lab, we're interested in the social brain, that is"},{"time":257418,"text":"the network of brain regions that we use to understand"},{"time":261002,"text":"other people and to interact with other people."},{"time":263435,"text":"So I like to show a photograph of a soccer game"},{"time":267201,"text":"to illustrate two aspects of how your social brains work."},{"time":271608,"text":"So this is a soccer game. (Laughter)"},{"time":273041,"text":"Michael Owen has just missed a goal, and he's lying"},{"time":275683,"text":"on the ground, and the first aspect of the social brain"},{"time":278485,"text":"that this picture really nicely illustrates is how automatic"},{"time":281444,"text":"and instinctive social emotional responses are,"},{"time":284494,"text":"so within a split second of Michael Owen missing this goal,"},{"time":287458,"text":"everyone is doing the same thing with their arms"},{"time":289268,"text":"and the same thing with their face, even Michael Owen"},{"time":291071,"text":"as he slides along the grass, is doing the same thing"},{"time":292895,"text":"with his arms, and presumably has a similar"},{"time":295164,"text":"facial expression, and the only people who don't"},{"time":297138,"text":"are the guys in yellow at the back — (Laughs) —"},{"time":300599,"text":"and I think they're on the wrong end of the stadium,"},{"time":303142,"text":"and they're doing another social emotional response"},{"time":305437,"text":"that we all instantly recognize, and that's the second aspect"},{"time":308072,"text":"of the social brain that this picture really nicely illustrates,"},{"time":311708,"text":"how good we are at reading other people's behavior,"},{"time":315090,"text":"their actions, their gestures, their facial expressions,"},{"time":317767,"text":"in terms of their underlying emotions and mental states."},{"time":321583,"text":"So you don't have to ask any of these guys."},{"time":323360,"text":"You have a pretty good idea of what they're feeling"},{"time":325901,"text":"and thinking at this precise moment in time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328489,"text":"So that's what we're interested in looking at in my lab."},{"time":330245,"text":"So in my lab, we bring adolescents and adults into the lab"},{"time":333833,"text":"to have a brain scan, we give them some kind of task"},{"time":336218,"text":"that involves thinking about other people, their minds,"},{"time":339512,"text":"their mental states, their emotions, and one of the findings"},{"time":342406,"text":"that we've found several times now, as have other labs"},{"time":345252,"text":"around the world, is part of the prefrontal cortex called"},{"time":348470,"text":"medial prefrontal cortex, which is shown in blue on the slide,"},{"time":351688,"text":"and it's right in the middle of prefrontal cortex"},{"time":354444,"text":"in the midline of your head."},{"time":356842,"text":"This region is more active in adolescents when they make"},{"time":360125,"text":"these social decisions and think about other people"},{"time":362252,"text":"than it is in adults, and this is actually a meta-analysis"},{"time":365053,"text":"of nine different studies in this area from labs around"},{"time":368293,"text":"the world, and they all show the same thing, that activity"},{"time":370993,"text":"in this medial prefrontal cortex area decreases"},{"time":374363,"text":"during the period of adolescence."},{"time":376810,"text":"And we think that might be because adolescents and adults"},{"time":379454,"text":"use a different mental approach, a different"},{"time":381820,"text":"cognitive strategy, to make social decisions,"},{"time":385238,"text":"and one way of looking at that is to do behavioral studies"},{"time":388754,"text":"whereby we bring people into the lab and we give them"},{"time":390731,"text":"some kind of behavioral task, and I'll just give you"},{"time":393275,"text":"another example of the kind of task that we use in my lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396485,"text":"So imagine that you're the participant in one of our"},{"time":399133,"text":"experiments. You come into the lab,"},{"time":400858,"text":"you see this computerized task."},{"time":403532,"text":"In this task, you see a set of shelves."},{"time":406322,"text":"Now, there are objects on these shelves, on some of them,"},{"time":409139,"text":"and you'll notice there's a guy standing behind the set"},{"time":412110,"text":"of shelves, and there are some objects that he can't see."},{"time":415695,"text":"They're occluded, from his point of view, with a kind of"},{"time":417974,"text":"gray piece of wood."},{"time":420618,"text":"This is the same set of shelves from his point of view."},{"time":424102,"text":"Notice that there are only some objects that he can see,"},{"time":427595,"text":"whereas there are many more objects that you can see."},{"time":430047,"text":"Now your task is to move objects around."},{"time":432243,"text":"The director, standing behind the set of shelves,"},{"time":434605,"text":"is going to direct you to move objects around,"},{"time":437350,"text":"but remember, he's not going to ask you to move objects"},{"time":439244,"text":"that he can't see. This introduces a really interesting"},{"time":442964,"text":"condition whereby there's a kind of conflict"},{"time":445157,"text":"between your perspective and the director's perspective."},{"time":448325,"text":"So imagine he tells you to move the top truck left."},{"time":451565,"text":"There are three trucks there. You're going to instinctively"},{"time":453611,"text":"go for the white truck, because that's the top truck"},{"time":455761,"text":"from your perspective, but then you have to remember,"},{"time":458579,"text":"\"Oh, he can't see that truck, so he must mean"},{"time":460638,"text":"me to move the blue truck,\" which is the top truck"},{"time":463395,"text":"from his perspective. Now believe it or not,"},{"time":466040,"text":"normal, healthy, intelligent adults like you make errors"},{"time":468991,"text":"about 50 percent of the time on that kind of trial."},{"time":472131,"text":"They move the white truck instead of the blue truck."},{"time":474974,"text":"So we give this kind of task to adolescents and adults,"},{"time":478290,"text":"and we also have a control condition"},{"time":479844,"text":"where there's no director and instead we give people a rule."},{"time":483905,"text":"We tell them, okay, we're going to do exactly the same thing"},{"time":485819,"text":"but this time there's no director. Instead you've got to"},{"time":488656,"text":"ignore objects with the dark gray background."},{"time":491863,"text":"You'll see that this is exactly the same condition, only"},{"time":494563,"text":"in the no-director condition they just have to remember"},{"time":497409,"text":"to apply this somewhat arbitrary rule, whereas"},{"time":500480,"text":"in the director condition, they have to remember"},{"time":502160,"text":"to take into account the director's perspective"},{"time":505701,"text":"in order to guide their ongoing behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509998,"text":"Okay, so if I just show you the percentage errors"},{"time":512608,"text":"in a large developmental study we did,"},{"time":515174,"text":"this is in a study ranging from age seven to adulthood,"},{"time":518728,"text":"and what you're going to see is the percentage errors"},{"time":519938,"text":"in the adult group in both conditions,"},{"time":521927,"text":"so the gray is the director condition, and you see"},{"time":525198,"text":"that our intelligent adults are making errors about 50 percent"},{"time":527771,"text":"of the time, whereas they make far fewer errors"},{"time":530486,"text":"when there's no director present, when they just have"},{"time":532514,"text":"to remember that rule of ignoring the gray background."},{"time":535595,"text":"Developmentally, these two conditions develop"},{"time":538263,"text":"in exactly the same way. Between late childhood"},{"time":541186,"text":"and mid-adolescence, there's an improvement,"},{"time":543427,"text":"in other words a reduction of errors, in both of these trials,"},{"time":546778,"text":"in both of these conditions."},{"time":547898,"text":"But it's when you compare the last two groups,"},{"time":550183,"text":"the mid-adolescent group and the adult group"},{"time":552135,"text":"where things get really interesting, because there, there is"},{"time":555295,"text":"no continued improvement in the no-director condition."},{"time":558333,"text":"In other words, everything you need to do in order to"},{"time":561263,"text":"remember the rule and apply it seems to be fully developed"},{"time":563969,"text":"by mid-adolescence, whereas in contrast,"},{"time":566500,"text":"if you look at the last two gray bars, there's still"},{"time":568897,"text":"a significant improvement in the director condition"},{"time":572047,"text":"between mid-adolescence and adulthood, and what"},{"time":574488,"text":"this means is that the ability to take into account someone"},{"time":577864,"text":"else's perspective in order to guide ongoing behavior,"},{"time":581149,"text":"which is something, by the way, that we do in everyday life all"},{"time":583408,"text":"the time, is still developing in mid-to-late adolescence."},{"time":588014,"text":"So if you have a teenage son or a daughter and you"},{"time":590554,"text":"sometimes think they have problems taking other people's"},{"time":592963,"text":"perspectives, you're right. They do. And this is why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596719,"text":"So we sometimes laugh about teenagers."},{"time":600232,"text":"They're parodied, sometimes even demonized in the media"},{"time":604095,"text":"for their kind of typical teenage behavior. They take risks,"},{"time":607622,"text":"they're sometimes moody, they're very self-conscious."},{"time":610393,"text":"I have a really nice anecdote from a friend of mine"},{"time":612886,"text":"who said that the thing he noticed most"},{"time":615373,"text":"about his teenage daughters before and after puberty"},{"time":618354,"text":"was their level of embarrassment in front of him."},{"time":620614,"text":"So, he said, \"Before puberty, if my two daughters"},{"time":623103,"text":"were messing around in a shop, I'd say, 'Hey,"},{"time":625357,"text":"stop messing around and I'll sing your favorite song,'"},{"time":627106,"text":"and instantly they'd stop messing around and he'd sing"},{"time":629007,"text":"their favorite song. After puberty, that became the threat."},{"time":632478,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":634295,"text":"The very notion of their dad singing in public"},{"time":637772,"text":"was enough to make them behave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640135,"text":"So people often ask,"},{"time":641563,"text":"\"Well, is adolescence a kind of recent phenomenon?"},{"time":644196,"text":"Is it something we've invented recently in the West?\""},{"time":646318,"text":"And actually, the answer is probably not. There are lots"},{"time":648986,"text":"of descriptions of adolescence in history that sound"},{"time":652409,"text":"very similar to the descriptions we use today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654566,"text":"So there's a famous quote by Shakespeare from \"The Winter's Tale\""},{"time":658799,"text":"where he describes adolescence as follows:"},{"time":661574,"text":"\"I would there were no age between ten and"},{"time":664420,"text":"three-and-twenty, or that youth would sleep out the rest;"},{"time":667660,"text":"for there is nothing in the between but getting wenches"},{"time":669751,"text":"with child, wronging the ancientry, stealing, fighting.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":675974,"text":"He then goes on to say, \"Having said that, would any"},{"time":680508,"text":"but these boiled brains of nineteen and two-and-twenty"},{"time":683653,"text":"hunt in this weather?\" (Laughter)"},{"time":686151,"text":"So almost 400 years ago, Shakespeare was portraying"},{"time":689077,"text":"adolescents in a very similar light to the light that we"},{"time":691801,"text":"portray them in today, but today we try to understand"},{"time":695260,"text":"their behavior in terms of the underlying changes"},{"time":698347,"text":"that are going on in their brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700285,"text":"So for example, take risk-taking. We know that adolescents"},{"time":703893,"text":"have a tendency to take risks. They do."},{"time":706218,"text":"They take more risks than children or adults,"},{"time":708850,"text":"and they are particularly prone to taking risks"},{"time":711310,"text":"when they're with their friends. There's an important drive"},{"time":714278,"text":"to become independent from one's parents"},{"time":716764,"text":"and to impress one's friends in adolescence."},{"time":719588,"text":"But now we try to understand that in terms of"},{"time":722187,"text":"the development of a part of their brain called the limbic system,"},{"time":725180,"text":"so I'm going to show you the limbic system in red"},{"time":727723,"text":"in the slide behind me, and also on this brain."},{"time":729588,"text":"So the limbic system is right deep inside the brain,"},{"time":732697,"text":"and it's involved in things like emotion processing"},{"time":736430,"text":"and reward processing. It gives you the rewarding feeling"},{"time":739580,"text":"out of doing fun things, including taking risks."},{"time":742876,"text":"It gives you the kick out of taking risks."},{"time":745241,"text":"And this region, the regions within the limbic system,"},{"time":748289,"text":"have been found to be hypersensitive to the rewarding"},{"time":751708,"text":"feeling of risk-taking in adolescents compared with adults,"},{"time":755477,"text":"and at the very same time, the prefrontal cortex,"},{"time":759179,"text":"which you can see in blue in the slide here,"},{"time":761453,"text":"which stops us taking excessive risks,"},{"time":764320,"text":"is still very much in development in adolescents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767718,"text":"So brain research has shown that the adolescent brain"},{"time":771385,"text":"undergoes really quite profound development,"},{"time":774727,"text":"and this has implications for education, for rehabilitation,"},{"time":778683,"text":"and intervention. The environment, including teaching,"},{"time":782703,"text":"can and does shape the developing adolescent brain,"},{"time":786112,"text":"and yet it's only relatively recently that we have been"},{"time":788914,"text":"routinely educating teenagers in the West."},{"time":791419,"text":"All four of my grandparents, for example, left school"},{"time":795172,"text":"in their early adolescence. They had no choice."},{"time":799006,"text":"And that's still the case for many, many teenagers"},{"time":801780,"text":"around the world today. Forty percent of teenagers"},{"time":804947,"text":"don't have access to secondary school education."},{"time":809169,"text":"And yet, this is a period of life where the brain is"},{"time":811808,"text":"particularly adaptable and malleable."},{"time":814655,"text":"It's a fantastic opportunity for learning and creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818425,"text":"So what's sometimes seen as the problem"},{"time":820658,"text":"with adolescents — heightened risk-taking, poor impulse"},{"time":823134,"text":"control, self-consciousness — shouldn't be stigmatized."},{"time":827076,"text":"It actually reflects changes in the brain that provide"},{"time":829913,"text":"an excellent opportunity for education"},{"time":832827,"text":"and social development. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":837257,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}